  "prompt": "Where does the word \"suicide\" come from?",
  "response": "The word \"suicide\" originates from the Latin word \"suicidium,\" which is derived from \"sui,\" meaning \"of oneself,\" and \"cidium,\" which comes from \"caedere,\" meaning \"to kill.\" Thus, \"suicide\" essentially means \"to kill oneself.\" The term began to be used in English in the mid-17th century, and it has since become a standard term to describe the act of intentionally ending one's own life.",
